Author-Name:    Young, Alwyn
Title:   Invention and Bounded Learning by Doing. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 443-72
Issue: 3
Volume: 101
Year: 1993
Month:  June 
Abstract:
  This paper attempts to integrate traditional models of invention and
 learning by doing, developing a model that emphasizes the interdependence
 between research activity in the laboratory and production experience on
 the factory floor. Learning depends on invention in that learning by doing
 is viewed as the exploration of the finite and bounded productive
 potential of invented technologies. At the same time, the profitability of
 costly invention is dependent on learning in that costs of production
 depend on cumulative learning experience.  Copyright 1993 by University of Chicago Press.
