Author-Name:    Porter, Robert H
Author-Name:  Zona, J Douglas
Title:   Detection of Bid Rigging in Procurement Auctions. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 518-38
Issue: 3
Volume: 101
Year: 1993
Month:  June 
Abstract:
  This paper examines bidding in auctions for state highway construction
 contracts, in order to determine whether bid rigging occurred. Detection
 of collusion is possible because of limited participation in the collusive
 scheme. Collusion did not take the form of a bid rotation scheme. Instead,
 several ring members bid on most jobs. One was a serious bidder, and the
 other submitted phony higher bids. The bids of noncartel firms, as well as
 their rank distribution, were related to cost measures. In contrast, the
 rank distribution of higher cartel bids was unrelated to similar cost
 measures and differed from that of the low cartel bid.  Copyright 1993 by University of Chicago Press.
