Title:   Monitoring Costs in Chinese Agricutural Teams. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 539-53
Issue: 3
Volume: 101
Year: 1993
Month:  June 
Abstract:
  Large productivity gains have been observed in Chinese agriculture
 following the transition from collective farming to household contracting.
 Using a model of mutual monitoring in an egalitarian production team, the
 authors estimate that labor supervision absorbed about 10-20 percent of
 total labor time for a sample of Chinese agricultural teams during
 1970-76. These agency costs are lower than comparable estimates derived
 from aggregate data.  Copyright 1993 by University of Chicago Press.
